FBIS4-18998 "drweu071__a94005" FBIS-WEU-94-071-A Daily Report 13 April 1994 ANNEX Belgium Government Orders Ambassador To Leave Kigali Government Orders Ambassador To Leave Kigali BR1304075094 Brussels BELGA Database in French 1829 GMT 12 Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY BR1304075094 Brussels BELGA Database French BFN [Article signed MAR: "Crisis: Belgian Ambassador's Departure Confirmed"] [Text] Brussels, 12 Apr (BELGA) -- The Belgian Foreign Ministry officially confirmed Tuesday evening [12 April] that "it instructed Belgian Ambassador in Rwanda Johan Swinnen to leave the country for security reasons." Five members of the embassy will remain temporarily on duty at Kigali airport. They will leave the Rwandan capital when the evacuation is over, the Foreign Ministry added.
